Turkey Drafts Plan to Regulate Internet Commerce, Haberturk Says

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-04-11T05:15:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/turkey-drafts-plan-to-regulate-internet-commerce-haberturk-says.html
Turkey  is drawing up plans to
regulate and tax internet commerce, Haberturk newspaper
reported, without saying how it got the information.  Officials in Ankara aim to have the measures in place some
time in 2012, the newsaper said. The steps will focus on trade
with companies based outside Turkey and aims to capture tax on
purchases that exceed a 150-euro limit set by customs
authorities, it said.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
